> ### Name: show_boundaries
> ### Title: Show Available Boundary Functions
> ### Aliases: show_boundaries
> 
> ### ** Examples
> 
> show_boundaries()

── Available Boundary Functions 

O'Brien-Fleming (conservative early, relaxing late):
boundary_obf(alpha = 0.025) # Frequentist: control Type I error
boundary_obf(threshold = 0.95) # Bayesian: ends at 0.95 threshold

Pocock (similar threshold at all looks):
boundary_pocock(alpha = 0.025) # Frequentist: calibrated for error
boundary_pocock(threshold = 0.95) # Bayesian: constant 0.95 at all looks

Hwang-Shih-DeCani (flexible one-parameter family):
boundary_hsd(alpha = 0.025, gamma = -4)
gamma=-4: OBF-like, gamma=1: Pocock-like, gamma=0: linear

Linear interpolation:
boundary_linear(start = 0.99, end = 0.95)
Linear change from start to end threshold

Power family (flexible shape):
boundary_power(base = 0.95, rho = 2)
rho=2: OBF-like, rho=1: linear, rho<1: less conservative

Constant (simple fixed threshold):
boundary_constant(threshold = 0.95)
Same threshold at all looks

Example usage in build_conditions():
  constant = list(
    # Bayesian: OBF shape ending at 0.95 threshold
    thr_dec_eff = boundary_obf(threshold = 0.95),
    # Linear futility: lenient early (0.3), stricter late (0.5)
    thr_dec_fut = boundary_linear(0.30, 0.50)
  )
> 
> 
